Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1} into strips. Halve and peel @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced); thinly slice one half. Finely chop remaining onion until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4 servings).

In a #small pot{}, combine @jasmine rice{1/2%cup}, @water{1%cup}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-20%minutes}. TIP: If rice is al dente, add water 1 TBSP at a time until rice is tender or reaches desired texture.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a large drizzle of @cooking oil{4%tsp} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper and sliced onion; cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add @shredded collard greens{3%oz}; cook, stirring, until slightly softened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Stir in half the @chicken stock concentrate{2}, half the @hot sauce{1%tsp}, @water{1/4%cup}, @sugar{1%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}. (For 4 servings, use as much hot sauce as you like, 1⁄3 cup water, and 2 tsp sugar). Cook, stirring constantly, until collards are wilted and liquid has evaporated, ~{3-5%minutes} more. Turn off heat.

> Prefer softer collard greens? Add another splash of water and cook 3-4 minutes more.

Pat @chicken cutlets{10%oz} dry with #paper towels{}; place in a #medium bowl{}. Season all over with @fry seasoning{1%tbsp}, half the @flour{2%tbsp}, @dried thyme{1%tsp} (3/4 tsp for 4 servings), salt, and pepper; turn to coat.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until browned and cooked through, ~{4-5%minutes} per side.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #cutting board{} to rest. Wipe out pan.

> Swap in chicken for pork; cook 3-5 minutes per side.

Melt @butter{1%tbsp} (2 TBSP for 4 servings) in pan used for pork over medium heat. Add chopped onion; cook, stirring, until softened and fragrant, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add a drizzle of oil, remaining flour, and 1/4 tsp thyme (be sure to measure); cook, stirring, until lightly browned, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Whisk in @beef stock concentrate{1}, remaining chicken stock concentrates, and @water{1%cup}. Simmer, whisking, until thickened, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Reduce heat to low. Season with salt and pepper to taste.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted. Season with salt to taste.

Slice pork crosswise.

Divide rice, pork, and veggies between plates. Spoon gravy over pork and serve.